insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('1', '3', 'My First Collection', '<p>Text pages can be grouped into collections so you can bind presentation content in a way that suits the type of your webiste. Each text collection can have a name, description and multiple text pages you define.</p><p>To edit the name and description of a text collection go to your Administration Tool -> Content Management, select a collection and then click edit on the right side.</p><p>There are various other content types the I-Metrics CMS supports and each collection is displayed with the content type next to it under the Content Management tool.</p><p>In order for a text collection to be accessed on your website it needs to have its visibility enabled. The visibility switch defines whether or not a collection displays its name and description on the web-front. Not whether associated text pages will be displayed.</p>', '2007-09-24 19:25:18', '2010-04-11 10:11:24', '100', '1');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('8', '3', 'Header Links', '<p>A group of titles with links to text pages to aid navigation of the web-front. This collection may be used if you display links on the header section of the template.</p><p>There is a dedicated configuration switch for that and by default the <b>header links</b> is binded to, in Site Content -> Configuration. It is called <b>Header Text Pages Group</b></p><p>By default the visibility of the header links is hidden as the header code retrieves associated text pages via the configuration switch reference and not by directly accessing this collection.</p>', '2009-06-29 15:56:54', '2010-04-11 09:18:23', '100', '0');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('10', '3', 'Archived', '<p>Each collection including the <b>Archives</b> can have a description. Topics and Articles from the previous year can be placed here or you can setup another text collection for archiving purposes.</p> <p>To reassign another collection for this purpose goto your Site Content -> Configuration, locate the <b>Archives zone</b> switch, edit it and then select another text collection from the list.</p><p>The archived collection could been a mixed collection. The type of the collection can only be defined when you create a new collection.To create a new collection use the <b>new button</b> on the right-hand side of the Content Management page on the administration end.</p><p>Usually collections contain a brief description as exposing a list of the associated entries is the main objective. As you can see below, the list of archived pages contains just the first paragraph of their actual page content. This is done automatically, but the behavior can always be re-coded by changing couple of lines of code.</p>', '2009-11-14 14:27:06', '2010-04-11 09:39:29', '100', '1');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('11', '3', 'Footer Links', '<p>Another collection of titles with links to text pages to aid navigation of the web-front. This collection may be used if you display links on the footer section of the template. Of course the footer could been a mixed collection as long as there is some code to decode mixed collections in the footer.tpl</p><p>There is a dedicated configuration switch for that and by default the <b>footer links</b> is binded to, in Site Content -> Configuration. It is called <b>Footer Text Pages Group</b></p><p>By default the visibility of the Footer Links is hidden as the footer code retrieves associated text pages via the configuration switch reference and not by directly accessing this collection.</p>', '2009-11-14 15:55:11', '2010-04-11 09:21:28', '100', '0');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('16', '3', 'E-Mail Templates', '<p>The E-Mail Templates is sample collection that represents a Personalized group of text pages, used to personalize the emails sent from your website.</p><p>Entries assigned to this collection may contain placeholders called personalized tags where the front end or back end scripts substitute the tags with specific pre-defined titles that targets a specific person with specific content.</p><p>Collections in general can be hidden from the web-front when they operate on the admin end only or when they have dedicated configuration switches for the front end template files.</p><p>When a collection becomes visible, its name and description can be displayed on the web-front upon  visitor\'s request. Displaying the name and brief description of a collection is not related with the content of entries or other collections assigned to this collection.</p>', '2010-02-03 20:46:51', '2010-04-11 10:10:00', '100', '0');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('17', '3', 'Help Desk Templates', '<p>The Help Desk templates are used to accelerate email response to visitors.</p><p>In the email response page within the helpdesk system, a drop-down menu appears that allows the site owner to preselect a template and insert it to the message body.</p><p>The drop-down menu contains all the templates within this zone.</p><p>As this collection is exclusively used on the administrator end its visibility should be hidden.</p><p>Collection visibility means whether or not the collection can be directly accessed from the web-front not whether the text pages or images are accessible.</p>', '2010-02-05 18:53:35', '2010-04-11 09:26:37', '100', '0');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('18', '4', 'Drop-Down Menu', '<p>The drop down menu is a collection of mixed type, used by some templates and has two levels of display.</p><p>The first level is the top navigation bar that consists of collections assigned beneath this collection.</p><p>The second level consists of individual titles of text pages and image names subject to the collections used.</p><p>The Drop-Down Menu zone has its visibility set to hidden because there is a dedicated configuration switch called <b>Menu Collection</b>. The switch is available from the Site Content -> Configuration page.</p><p>Each of the dedicated configuration switches for the default collections can be reset to a different collection instantly.</p>', '2010-02-16 15:30:13', '2010-04-11 10:05:25', '100', '0');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('19', '5', 'My First Gallery', '<p>Similar to text collections, <b>Image Collections</b> consist of images grouped together and presented on the web-front.</p><p>This default image gallery can be configured from the administration end by accessing the Site Content -> Content Management tool. Once you reach that page locate and select the collection called <b>My First Gallery</b>. You can edit its name and this description by clicking the edit button on the right-hand side.</p><p>Associate images with this collection by clicking details or the arrow-down icon on the left-hand side.</p><p>The I-Metrics CMS offers an additional control that is specific for image collections, to upload images from your system into the server, along with an image browsing facility and image title and an image brief description. Up to 250 characters can be used for an image name and description </p><p>Sample images were taken from the <a href=\"http://www.public-domain-photos.com/\">Public Domain-Photos website</a></p>', '2010-02-25 18:29:19', '2010-04-10 17:31:13', '100', '1');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('20', '4', 'Right Side Entries', '<p>The Right Side Entries is a a carbon copy of the Left Side Entries. A mixed collection processed by the right navigation column code and plugins on the web-front.</p><p>It\'s visibility is hidden as there is a dedicated switch to select which collection to use for the right-side entries. The name of the configuration switch is <b>Right Side Collection</b> available from the Site Content -> Configuration page that is used as a reference by the code on the web-front.</p>', '2010-02-18 16:59:56', '2010-04-11 09:51:53', '100', '0');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('21', '4', 'Sitemap', '<p>The Sitemap provides an easy way to locate the main topics of this site.</p><p>The I-Metrics CMS deploys a special type of content called <b>Mixed Collections</b>. If you check under your administration end Site Content -> Content Management, you will see a collection called <b>Sitemap</b>. So the Sitemap is basically another collection.</p><p> Mixed collections may contain any other type collection including any other mixed collections except for themselves. For instance the first gallery, archived and right-side entries collections can all be set under the Sitemap. <p><p>I-Metrics CMS also deploys a multi-column mechanism to split the collection contents into multiple columns.</p>', '2010-02-20 14:57:34', '2010-04-10 17:43:00', '100', '1');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('22', '5', 'My Second Gallery', '<p>Another image gallery here demonstrates the flexibility of this web-package. The I-Metrics CMS can display multiple collections of images on the various sections of the template.</p><p>Images within a collection can be ordered using the sequence column and assigning a number to it. The lower the number the higher the importance images. </p><p>The title and description of an image can be changed at any time from the Content Management section on the administration end. To access the individual images select the collection that contains the images.</p><p>In this case <b>My Second Gallery</b> is an image collection so select it, click the left-side icon or the details button on the right. Then alter the name and description of each image. At the end hit tick the checkboxes of the entries you changed and hit the update button.</p><p>Sample images were taken from the <a href=\"http://www.public-domain-photos.com/\">Public Domain-Photos website</a></p>', '2010-04-10 17:08:00', '2010-04-10 17:30:59', '101', '1');
insert into abstract_zones (abstract_zone_id, abstract_types_id, abstract_zone_name, abstract_zone_desc, date_added, last_modified, sort_id, status_id) values ('23', '4', 'Left Side Entries', '<p>The Left Side Entries is a mixed collection and is processed by the left navigation column code and plugins on the web-front.</p><p>It\'s visibility is hidden as there is a dedicated switch to select which collection to use for the left-side entries. The name of the configuration switch is <b>Left Side Collection</b> available from the Site Content -> Configuration page</p>', '2010-04-10 21:27:17', '2010-04-11 09:49:24', '100', '0');
