insert into gtext (gtext_id, gtext_title, gtext_description, date_added, status, sub) values ('10', 'Home Page', '<p><a class=\"pg_link\" title=\"labyrinth\" rel=\"home\" href=\"images/sample-labyrinth.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"textimage\" style=\"float: left;\" title=\"labyrinth\" src=\"fly_thumb.php?img=images/sample-labyrinth.jpg&amp;w=240&amp;h=180\" alt=\"labyrinth\" /></a>The Home Page displayed here is used for demonstration purposes for the content of the home page. The I-Metrics CMS organizes text pages into text content collections. Text Content Collections are groups of text pages you define using the Site Content system. </p>
<p>The home page with the stock configuration does not appear in other content collections. At any time you can switch the page that displays as the home page using the Site Content -&gt; Configuration -&gt;Default Front Page. Therefore any text page can become the home page by changing this configuration. Alternatively you can edit the content of this page by going to the Site Content -&gt; Text Pages and locate the entry named <strong>Home Page</strong>.</p>
<p>If you need to add images to a text page you can there are 2 tiny images at the bottom of this section as you edit the page from the administration end. The first to insert existing images on the server, into the page content. The second to upload images from your system into the server.</p>
<p>Editing pages should be straight forward with the built-in word-processor. You can always paste HTML content using the HTML button of the word-processor as part of the text content. Once you complete the page you can hit the update button, to save the changes. </p>
<p>If you gone through the installation process you had the chance to select one of the pre-packaged templates. Each of these templates has its own features some display both navigation columns others display only one and some display a drop-down menu. Coupled with your content a template theme can better represent the type of your business or blog and expose important pages. </p>
<p>The basic template related files can be found under the <strong>includes/template</strong> folder on the web-front of your site. Various plugins may add new files to the template sub-folders. The gathering of the template files under a single folder enables site owners and web-developers to modify the template properties and resources easily.</p>', '2010-02-25', '0', '1');
